\f0\fs32 \cf2 South (sand dunes, Victoria Falls, Robben Island)
\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400

\f0\b0\fs30 \cf0 You start your trip in southern Africa. The first place you stop is Swakopmund. Here, you get to ride a quad bike through the sand dunes. Being surrounded by sand for miles creates an almost otherworldly feel, almost like you\'92re on Mars. The sky is bluer than you\'92ve ever seen. After traveling to Zambia, you make a pilgrimmage to Victoria Falls, the largest waterfall on Earth. It\'92s so misty there that it feels like it\'92s constantly raining. You\'92re soaked. It\'92s worth it. After resting up a day in South Africa, you take a ferry to Robben Island, where Nelson Mandela was kept imprisoned. In his cell, there are three thin blankets and no bed. You hear it gets cold there in the winter.
