\f0\fs32 \cf2 North (pyramids, Church of St. George, Erta Ale volcano)
\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400

\f0\b0\fs30 \cf0 You take a bus to the pyramids in Egypt. Once you get off the bus, a man grabs you and does not stop yelling that the only way to get to the pyramids is a $200 camel ride. Once you arrive, you see plenty of tourists arriving on foot. The next day, you go to the Church of St. George in Ethiopia, which is carved out of stone underground. On the way, you see a girl sitting in the street, probably no more than 10 years old. She holds your gaze until the bus departs. On the last day of your trip, you visit Erta Ale, a continuously active volcano with a lava lake, which is a pretty big deal considering that there are only 6 lava lakes in the world.
